        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 8 at 2:09PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 209 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Raton, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Raton.

This includes the following highways...
Highway 64 between Mile Markers 341 and 368.
Interstate 25 between Mile Markers 443 and 453.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.

Accumulations of small hail on roads can create very slick and
hazardous driving conditions.</instruction>
